<HEADLINE>
FT  01 AUG 94 / UK Company News: Bredero to lose listing on September 1
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Bredero Properties, the property developer that was almost dragged down by
its ambitious Centre West development in Hammersmith, will lose its listing
on September 1 after Slough Estates succeeded in gaining an 81.8 per cent
stake.
Slough received 32.3 per cent acceptances for its 10p a share privatisation
offer, adding to its initial 49.4 per cent stake in the company.
It is unclear whether British Land has accepted the offer, after taking a 7
per cent stake in Bredero in June.
</TEXT>
