<HEADLINE>
FT  01 AUG 94 / Arts (Openings): Oslo
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Oslo Chamber Music Festival, founded in 1989 by Norwegian violinist Arve
Tellefsen, devotes its programme this year to Britain. The opening concert
on Friday features songs by Dowland and Vaughan Williams, and later
programmes range from Byrd and Bridge to David Matthews and Oliver Knussen.
The Nash and Hilliard Ensembles are taking part, while Norwegian cellist
Truls Mork plays the Elgar concerto.
</TEXT>
