<HEADLINE>
FT  01 AUG 94 / Arts (Openings): Amsterdam
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A major survey of Renaissance prints opens at the Rijskmuseum on Saturday.
The exhibition is devoted to the years 1470-1500, and aims to show how
masters from different countries, including Mantegna, Durer and Lucas van
Leyden, contributed to the rapid development of printmaking techniques and
functions. The selection includes some private loans which have never been
exhibited before.
</TEXT>
