<HEADLINE>
FT  01 AUG 94 / Arts (Openings): Proms
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A bumper four-hour Prom on Sunday pays tribute to the work of Sir William
Glock. In his years as controller of music at the BBC from 1959 to 1972 the
adventurous Glock opened up new frontiers at the BBC Proms, bringing in
music old and new. His enthusiasms ranged from Josquin to Stockhausen and
only a concert of exceptional scope could hope to do justice to them all.
The conductors on Sunday include Pierre Boulez, Colin Davis and George
Benjamin.
</TEXT>
