demonstrators. A four-week strike which has already forced a 300,000 barrels
a day cut in oil production - about 20 per cent of normal output - is set to
intensify this week. The Nigeria Labour Congress, which represents over 40
main trade unions, has called a national strike from Wednesday. The Rev
Jesse Jackson, sent by the White House last week to mediate in the crisis,
feared 'Nigeria only has a few more days to go, for the escalating tensions
might very well explode.'
