<HEADLINE>
FT  30 JUL 94 / Craxi sentenced to 8 1/2 years for bank fraud
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The former Socialist premier Bettino Craxi was sentenced to 8 1/2 years in
jail for fraudulent bankruptcy in the 1982 collapse of the Banco Ambrosiano.
A similar sentence was handed out to Claudio Martelli, former Socialist
justice minister and one-time heir to Mr Craxi. Since February Mr Craxi has
been living at his seaside villa in Tunisia. He still has the right to
appeal.
</TEXT>
