<TEXT>
Stock index futures closed above the day's low point after a volatile
session dominated by worries over interest rates and weakness in the fixed
interest markets, writes Joel Kibazo.
The September futures contract on the FT-SE 100 closed at 3,095, at a 13
point premium to cash, but 8 below its previous finish. Volume was a healthy
20,728 lots. It opened at 3,112 and during the session, it touched a high of
3,124 and a low of 3,064.
In traded options, stock options made a significant contribution to the
day's total of 42,473 lots.
