<HEADLINE>
FT  30 JUL 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Prices of all grades of pepper rose considerably this week, reports Man
Producten. Indonesian shippers were most reluctant to offer any white pepper
because of disappointing and delayed arrivals of new crop and this helped to
push prices up by USDollars 250 to Dollars 300 a tonne. Spot white was on
offer at Dollars 3,300 and prompt shipment at Dollars 3,150, c and f. Black
pepper prices were also firmer across the board. Rising demand coupled with
limited supplies from most origins pushed prices to new highs. Black pepper
of fair average quality for spot delivery reached about Dollars 1,850 a
tonne and better grades were traded at about Dollars 2,000. In the US market
the spot price exceeded 90 cents a pound.
</TEXT>
