FT  30 JUL 94 / Letters to the Editor: Air France support should be decided
on a commercial basis
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Dr MIKE WALKER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, In your editorial, 'Flight plan for Air France' (July 25), you argue
that state aid to Air France should be tied to a deadline for the full
privatisation of Air France. Why wait until after the provision of state
aid? As you rightly say, the lack of a market for shares in Air France makes
it difficult to judge whether state aid is being granted on commercial
terms. However, if Air France were privatised, the market could decide
whether or not it was a sensible commercial decision to invest another
FFr20bn in Air France. If it is a sensible commercial decision, then the
funds could be raised on the markets; if it is not, then the funds would not
be forthcoming.
