The Court of Appeal rejected argument that the 253-day Brittania Park trial
was so long and complex that the jury must have been unable to concentrate
sufficiently to reach a safe and satisfactory verdict.
Mr Peter Kellard, Mr Edward Dwyer and Mr John Wright, former chairman of the
Derbyshire theme park, were convicted in 1992 of offences including
fraudulent trading.
