<HEADLINE>
FT  30 JUL 94 / Eurotunnel set for passenger licence
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN WILLMAN, Public Policy Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The go-ahead for passenger train services to run through the Channel tunnel
is expected very shortly, Eurotunnel said yesterday. It understood that the
Anglo-French Intergovernmental Commission, which must approve passenger
services, met on Thursday to make its decision.
Eurotunnel said it had completed its presentations earlier this week to the
commission's safety authority, which must satisfy itself on the safety
aspects of train operations in the tunnel. Letters setting out the
commission's decision were expected very shortly.
The company, which already runs freight services, wants to operate passenger
services between London, Paris and Brussels and a tunnel shuttle service.
